[1] Cholera - Nigeria (Delta State)
Date: Wed, 28 Dec 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Independent [edited]
<http://www.independentng.com/nigerdelta/nddec280502.htm>

An outbreak of cholera in Opuama and Tsekelewu communities in the
Warri North Local Government Area of Delta State has reportedly
claimed about 5 lives, causing panic in the area. The epidemic, said
to have broken out last weekend, has been linked to bad drinking
water and an offensive odor from the shallow stream in the area.
Chairman of the Egbema Community Development Committee, Mr Evans
Abulu, who confirmed the incident via telephone, said: "There is this
cholera outbreak in Opuama and Tsekelewu and environs. It happened
about 2 days ago (Fri, 23 Dec 2005) and 5 persons have died. We are
working seriously so that we can send some health officers down
there."
Opuama and Tsekelewu had experienced a similar cholera outbreak in
2002, which claimed some lives before it was brought under control.
Another incident in Oshimili South Local Governmenet Area in Dec 2004
had also claimed over 17 lives, including that of a 70-year-old man.
[Byline: Tunke-Aye Bisina]
