[2] Cholera - Zambia (Lusaka)
Date: Tue, 27 Dec 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: TodayOnline.com [edited]
<http://www.todayonline.com/articles/92262.asp>
The number of cholera cases in Zambia has almost quadrupled since Nov
2005, reaching 900, with the bulk of infections being in the capital,
Health Minister Sylvia Masebo said. Masebo said cases had shot up
from 233 -- of which 7 were fatal -- in Nov 2005 to the latest figure
as a result of the onset of the rainy season, which has helped the
water-borne disease to spread.
"About 90 percent of the cases have been recorded in Lusaka. We are
urging people to avoid unnecessary gatherings to prevent the further
spread of the disease," Masebo said Tue, 27 Dec 2005. She added that
an updated fatality figure was not yet available.
Masebo said the government had opened up cholera centers where those
affected have been quarantined.
--
