[4] Cholera - Uganda (Hoima District)
Date: Fri, 30 Dec 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Monitor [edited]
<http://www.monitor.co.ug/news/reg12303.php>

At least 3 people have died and over 10 are undergoing treatment due
to a fresh outbreak of cholera at Kaiso Landing Site on Lake Albert
in Buseruka sub-county, Hoima district.
According to Kaiso LCI Chairman Henry Irumba, the 3 were buried on
Wed, 28 Dec 2005. Irumba asked the District Director of Health
services, Dr Joseph Ruyonga, to intervene. He attributed the outbreak
to unsafe water at the lake and lack of facilities to purify water
for drinking.
By the time of filing this story, the District Director of Health
Services was not in office, and his number could not be reached. But
the District Health Inspector, Mr Christopher Asiimwe, said they
would dispatch a health team to conduct health education and also
treat the patients.
[Byline: Ausi Balyesiima]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
