[5] Cholera - Uganda (Kampala District)
Date: Mon, 26 Dec 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Daily Monitor [edited]
<http://www.monitor.co.ug/news/news12268.php>

The cholera epidemic in Bwaise has increased due to flooding. The
(LC2) chairperson Bwaise 3 Parish, Kawempe division, Hajati Nuruh
Balinda Nakanjako, has said people living along the water channels
dump garbage in the channels and others empty their toilets into the
channels. "Bwaise 3 is mostly affected because this is where garbage
from different places gathers, causing floods," Nakanjako said.
She was speaking during a project to clear the Nsooba drainage at
Katoogo zone. Nakanjako criticised Kawempe division authorities for
not fulfilling their promise of clearing the channels every 3 months.
[Byline: Ephraim Kasozi]
--
